1
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,400
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,680
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:40,080
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,520
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 6]

23
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,690
Don't call me 'Mentor' outside.

24
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,930
Why so shy all of a sudden?

25
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:52,180
Then what should I call you?

26
00:01:53,510 --> 00:01:54,020
Bro?

27
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:55,490
Cong?

28
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:57,980
Or Mr. Guo?

29
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:58,850
Guo…

30
00:01:59,120 --> 00:01:59,980
Just use my full name.

31
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:03,050
That sounds so rude!

32
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,000
Guo Cong…

33
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,520
Guo Cong…

34
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:06,960
I…

35
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:09,290
Just let me call you 'Mentor'.

36
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,060
Or I'll keep it low.

37
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:12,820
Just bear with it, Mentor.

38
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:14,060
Okay?

39
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:14,980
Here, take this.

40
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,730
What's this?

41
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:20,500
Aren't we here to practice
sizing people up at a glance?

42
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,100
Why switch to sketching?

43
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,690
Sizing people up at a glance

44
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:26,380
means observing someone

45
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,890
in the shortest time.

46
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,450
You need to watch their faces,

47
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:33,100
behavior,

48
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,380
and subtle shifts in expression

49
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:37,730
so you can tell

50
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:38,610
who they are,

51
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:39,170
what they want,

52
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:39,690
and why

53
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:40,890
they're here.

54
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,500
Find the key point

55
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,540
and draw it.

56
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:44,730
Draw it?

57
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:47,500
Can't I just take a photo with my phone?

58
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,850
You're gonna shoot right at their faces?

59
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:53,060
I can take photos from afar.

60
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:55,500
A good camera can't beat a quick sketch.

61
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:56,690
Drawing

62
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:57,780
trains you.

63
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,540
It sharpens your memory

64
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,260
and guides your focus.

65
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:06,690
Do I really have to?

66
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:10,290
What if I'm a terrible drawer?

67
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:12,100
You're not taking an art exam.

68
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,290
Why so nervous?

69
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,690
No need to draw everything,

70
00:03:15,710 --> 00:03:16,890
just parts.

71
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:18,340
Like their eyes,

72
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:19,380
noses, mouths,

73
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:21,500
hand movements,

74
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,100
or a pet nearby.

75
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,940
But there's a key,

76
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,410
which is

77
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,570
what you draw

78
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:27,260
must carry

79
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,730
useful information.

80
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,060
Got it.

81
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,730
If it looks ugly,

82
00:03:35,310 --> 00:03:36,690
don't laugh at me.

83
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:37,890
I said

84
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:39,220
focus on key points.

85
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:39,890
Alright.

86
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,380
Where do we draw?

87
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:42,410
Doesn't matter.

88
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,610
No fixed place.

89
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,660
Just anywhere with people.

90
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:45,690
Oh right,

91
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,690
one more thing.

92
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:49,340
Besides those key points,

93
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:50,780
you need to step

94
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:52,890
outside the subject

95
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:54,290
and watch how they

96
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:55,980
interact with other people

97
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,040
and also

98
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,690
with their surroundings.

99
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:01,890
Okay.

100
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:08,660
Look,

101
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,540
what are they doing?

102
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:13,660
A senior tour group

103
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,100
from the north.

104
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:17,050
First day here.

105
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,490
Not used to the weather,

106
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:19,980
so they're overdressed.

107
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,340
They're probably heading

108
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,140
to a landmark for photos.

109
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:27,610
Then, where

110
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,610
is their next stop?

111
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:30,460
If they're tourists,

112
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,900
next is likely the Longfu Temple

113
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,410
or the Lianta Mountain Park nearby.

114
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:37,100
Those are the only two places I know.

115
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,140
Who's missing

116
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,170
from that group?

117
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:42,220
Who's missing?

118
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,730
Where's the guide?

119
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,980
The guide…

120
00:04:57,270 --> 00:05:00,020
Folks, get on!

121
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:05,980
I got it!

122
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,850
There's a souvenir shop
at the right turn ahead.

123
00:05:10,630 --> 00:05:11,930
So they are going there

124
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:13,850
for souvenirs next.

125
00:05:14,510 --> 00:05:16,100
This is fun, Mentor!

126
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,580
A change in perspective

127
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,580
opens up a whole new world!

128
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,100
You've just opened

129
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,580
a new door for me!

130
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,020
Then go on in.

131
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:24,780
I'm leaving.

132
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:26,850
Wait.

133
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:27,370
Leaving?

134
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:28,700
Where are you going, Mentor?

135
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,340
Why are you leaving?

136
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:31,340
Mentor!

137
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:32,460
Mentor!

138
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:33,850
Are you the Monkey King or what?

139
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:35,700
'Mentor, Mentor' nonstop!

140
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,170
Submit your work before clocking in.

141
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:44,220
Yeah, I am the Monkey King.

142
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,930
I'm gonna master

143
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,410
this 'sharp vision' thing.

144
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,490
Take care,

145
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,900
Mentor!

146
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,780
Just staring at girls.

147
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:12,930
Got things done?

148
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:14,900
Don't worry, Li.

149
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,580
We got a tip from airport staff.

150
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,340
The day the doll showed up,

151
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,100
Qian Shengkai was at customs, too.

152
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:22,900
Qian Shengkai?

153
00:06:23,310 --> 00:06:23,900
That mule?

154
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:26,700
What was he doing there?

155
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:27,850
No idea yet.

156
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:30,780
The courier was too clean.

157
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,850
Nothing to trace back.

158
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:37,460
Even so, it couldn't be a coincidence.

159
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,250
Keep an eye on him
for the next few days.

160
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,340
No need for that, Li.

161
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,540
Why are you suddenly so careful?

162
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,660
Do what I tell you.

163
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:46,700
Okay.

164
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,020
What about Sa Ziyi?

165
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:51,900
Some were caught, and some fled.

166
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:54,540
Almost no one was left.

167
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,340
I heard

168
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,220
Sa Ziyi's man,

169
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,490
Long Shuo,

170
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,900
is out.

171
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:05,930
Long Shuo?

172
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,810
I remember him.

173
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,250
Have you found him?

174
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,250
Not yet.

175
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:15,370
He's probably not in Binhai.

176
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,580
You know, Sazi Yi's dead.

177
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,850
His backing and livelihood are gone.

178
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:21,730
Why stay in this place of bad memories?

179
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,540
What if he's sentimental?

180
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:25,730
Not everyone's like you.

181
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,850
Keep looking.

182
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:29,700
Li,

183
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:32,980
what about Mr. E?

184
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,460
Any movements? Should I…

185
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,730
Do your job

186
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,220
and shut up about the rest.

187
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:49,320
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

188
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,650
Strike the bamboo clappers.

189
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,610
No more delay. Let's talk about…

190
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,330
Our fall uniforms are here.

191
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:57,660
Wu Song avenged his brother

192
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,100
- and killed his sister-in-law…
- What are you doing?

193
00:07:59,710 --> 00:08:00,810
Turning in homework.

194
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:03,370
The higher court issued the order.

195
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:05,450
Dong Chao and Xue Ba
were assigned as escorts.

196
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:08,420
Dong Chao held the documents.

197
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:09,320
The three

198
00:08:09,420 --> 00:08:09,920
set out…

199
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:11,490
That's enough.

200
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,490
The show's almost up.

201
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:13,700
I'm just brushing up.

202
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,700
Alright, after work then.

203
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:29,980
I told you I'm bad at drawing.

204
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,180
Explain it.

205
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,130
What is this?

206
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,060
This is

207
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,100
a young man pushing a wheelchair

208
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,580
running across a skybridge.

209
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,370
In the wheelchair

210
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,940
sits an elderly person,

211
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,820
holding a pinwheel.

212
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,460
They both

213
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,370
look very happy.

214
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,340
I really

215
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,980
felt that happiness!

216
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:50,890
I have a question.

217
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,060
Zhang Yu,

218
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,770
is the elderly person a woman?

219
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:54,980
No, a man,

220
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,580
an old guy!

221
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,060
Then this hair…

222
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:57,980
It's so long…

223
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,370
No,

224
00:08:58,390 --> 00:08:59,220
that's not hair.

225
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,100
It's a coat.

226
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,850
Let the mentor teach.

227
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:04,820
Keep it down.

228
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,530
You keep it down.

229
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:10,220
We're practicing

230
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,100
observing people's relations.

231
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:13,250
The sketch is great.

232
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:14,250
Now tell me,

233
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,420
what's their relationship?

234
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,220
What makes you so sure the young man

235
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,420
was the old man's grandson?

236
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:21,250
That boy looked very young,

237
00:09:21,270 --> 00:09:23,460
maybe in his teens or early 20s.

238
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,490
If I were

239
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:26,060
a family member,

240
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,700
I wouldn't trust

241
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,130
such a young caregiver

242
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:31,010
with an elderly person.

243
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:31,940
So I think

244
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,460
he must be the old man's grandson.

245
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:34,610
Good!

246
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:35,340
Okay.

247
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:35,980
Very good!

248
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:36,700
Makes sense.

249
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,580
Alright, next one.

250
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,770
Fair point.

251
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,340
Next.

252
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,100
This one…

253
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:42,890
A potato.

254
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:43,730
Kinda looks like one.

255
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,650
- Stop! - This is…

256
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:45,820
Pause.

257
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,610
Xiaoyan, take a look.

258
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:48,370
Explain it.

259
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:49,890
Me?

260
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:52,770
This is a person.

261
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:54,700
Then…

262
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:55,530
I got it!

263
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:56,940
This is a man,

264
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,850
and this is his child.

265
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,490
They are a father and a son.

266
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:02,980
He's holding a stick
and is about to hit the kid,

267
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,340
and the kid is crying his eyes out.

268
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:04,650
Right?

269
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,730
Same here.

270
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:07,980
Nice, bro.

271
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,850
Aren't we right?

272
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,530
The kid must've been naughty,

273
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:13,300
so his dad was gonna hit him.

274
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:13,940
Stop!

275
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,180
This… Right,

276
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,180
it is a man.

277
00:10:18,630 --> 00:10:19,850
And this is his child.

278
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,730
But that's not a stick.

279
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,060
That's a cigarette.

280
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,420
A cigarette?

281
00:10:25,510 --> 00:10:26,610
Why?

282
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,460
Here's the thing.

283
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,220
There was a man

284
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,420
standing by the roadside.

285
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:33,460
His eyes

286
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:36,300
looked completely

287
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,100
lost and empty,

288
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,980
staring into the distance.

289
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:39,770
And

290
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,530
he was holding a cigarette,

291
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,180
but it was not lit.

292
00:10:43,630 --> 00:10:44,610
This is his son,

293
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,980
about five or six years old,

294
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,010
standing next to him

295
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,580
and grabbing his sleeve.

296
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:51,220
Zhang Yu,

297
