985
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,420
But bro,

986
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:24,090
we've been waiting so many days,

987
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:25,860
but we still haven't seen him.

988
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:29,860
He'll show up today.

989
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:30,740
Why?

990
00:37:31,110 --> 00:37:32,300
Because I told him

991
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:34,130
I found his daughter's school.

992
00:37:38,630 --> 00:37:39,460
Thanks.

993
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:40,860
- Please enjoy. - Thanks.

994
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:48,050
Got it, uncle.

995
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:48,900
Thanks.

996
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:50,650
When I'm off in a couple of days,

997
00:37:50,670 --> 00:37:51,650
I'll go fishing with you.

998
00:37:53,190 --> 00:37:53,650
Alright.

999
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:54,610
Hanging up, bye.

1000
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,420
Doesn't it taste sour?

1001
00:38:13,070 --> 00:38:13,900
It's fine.

1002
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:15,050
Mentor,

1003
00:38:15,070 --> 00:38:16,650
I looked it up online.

1004
00:38:16,670 --> 00:38:19,300
Yongding Manufacturing's
legal rep is Huang Qiang.

1005
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,260
The factory's been running
for five years,

1006
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:22,860
but it's high-risk

1007
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,260
involved in multiple debt lawsuits.

1008
00:38:25,070 --> 00:38:26,380
Almost as I thought.

1009
00:38:27,110 --> 00:38:28,860
Producing a single custom thermos.

1010
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:31,010
It looks strange.

1011
00:38:32,230 --> 00:38:34,490
If Huang Qiang still took it,

1012
00:38:34,510 --> 00:38:36,260
he must really need money.

1013
00:38:37,510 --> 00:38:41,050
And that thermos
definitely wasn't cheap.

1014
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,300
Look!

1015
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:13,530
Good at hiding, huh?

1016
00:39:14,710 --> 00:39:15,530
I just got here.

1017
00:39:15,550 --> 00:39:16,740
You're pretty good at hiding!

1018
00:39:17,150 --> 00:39:18,610
Bro, have a smoke.

1019
00:39:18,630 --> 00:39:19,380
I don't smoke.

1020
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,690
Quit it!

1021
00:39:21,590 --> 00:39:22,530
Where's my money?

1022
00:39:23,630 --> 00:39:24,380
Looks like

1023
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:26,170
that's Huang Qiang.

1024
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:34,780
I'm not asking you for a loan.

1025
00:39:35,190 --> 00:39:36,940
You know my situation.

1026
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:37,650
Do me a favor

1027
00:39:37,670 --> 00:39:39,490
and help me find some work.

1028
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:40,780
Business is tough these days.

1029
00:39:41,030 --> 00:39:41,820
Hanging up.

1030
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:42,690
I've got customers.

1031
00:39:42,710 --> 00:39:43,420
Mr. Li…!

1032
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:49,780
Doing well, everyone's around.

1033
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,690
Down bad, they run away like hell.

1034
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:27,980
Get out.

1035
00:40:29,230 --> 00:40:30,050
Get out!

1036
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:40,530
Mr. Huang,

1037
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:41,690
don't get me wrong.

1038
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:43,380
We're not collecting debts.

1039
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,460
I'm from China Customs.

1040
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:47,860
Got a minute?

1041
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:52,380
My daughter's birthday is tomorrow.

1042
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:54,980
I just want a quiet birthday with her.

1043
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,820
Can you stop bothering me?

1044
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,650
I've told your anti-smuggling men

1045
00:41:05,670 --> 00:41:06,940
everything I know.

1046
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:08,300
If you don't believe me,

1047
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,340
then just arrest me,

1048
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:10,380
and I'll get some peace.

1049
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,050
You may not understand.

1050
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:14,210
The thermos you made
was used by smugglers

1051
00:41:14,230 --> 00:41:15,300
to hide contraband.

1052
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,210
It almost caused

1053
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:17,490
serious losses to the country.

1054
00:41:17,510 --> 00:41:18,530
'Almost' means

1055
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:19,460
no loss, right?

1056
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,690
But I lost something!

1057
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,260
I was just taking a normal order.

1058
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,130
What did I do wrong?

1059
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,900
If you're willing to provide leads,

1060
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:26,650
we can catch the smugglers

1061
00:41:26,670 --> 00:41:28,300
and reduce losses for the country.

1062
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,490
I'm just a businessman.

1063
00:41:29,510 --> 00:41:30,940
I've got my own difficulties.

1064
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,170
Please just let me go.

1065
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:32,820
Don't worry.

1066
00:41:33,110 --> 00:41:35,050
All sources of information
will be kept confidential.

1067
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:36,570
Confidential? How?

1068
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:37,980
I made the thermos.

1069
00:41:38,230 --> 00:41:39,420
I'm the source.

1070
00:41:39,510 --> 00:41:40,490
You can't hide that!

1071
00:41:40,510 --> 00:41:41,530
I've got a family!

1072
00:41:41,550 --> 00:41:42,460
Who's got my back?

1073
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:43,010
Who's…

1074
00:41:43,030 --> 00:41:43,530
Mr. Huang,

1075
00:41:43,550 --> 00:41:44,460
you may not know it.

1076
00:41:44,670 --> 00:41:45,490
Binhai Customs

1077
00:41:45,510 --> 00:41:48,260
once solved a child drug-smuggling case.

1078
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:49,860
What does that have to do with me?

1079
00:41:52,110 --> 00:41:53,260
Some of those girls

1080
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:54,900
used as drug carriers by smugglers

1081
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:56,090
were teenagers,

1082
00:41:56,110 --> 00:41:57,610
and some were only four or five.

1083
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,130
They had to swallow

1084
00:42:00,150 --> 00:42:01,690
high-purity drug capsules,

1085
00:42:02,030 --> 00:42:03,820
like swallowing ticking bombs.

1086
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,650
They couldn't eat

1087
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:06,650
or drink water all day

1088
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,090
because once those capsules

1089
00:42:08,110 --> 00:42:09,010
rupture in their bodies,

1090
00:42:09,030 --> 00:42:10,340
they can die at any moment.

1091
00:42:10,510 --> 00:42:12,130
Those smugglers

1092
00:42:12,150 --> 00:42:12,690
have no bottom line at all

1093
00:42:12,710 --> 00:42:14,530
for making money.

1094
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:18,210
But in the end,

1095
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:20,690
those girls were rescued

1096
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:21,780
because of him.

1097
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:28,860
Back then, he had just joined Customs.

1098
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,900
To crack the case,

1099
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,570
he and his mentor

1100
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:34,340
chased down every lead,

1101
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:36,050
just like we're trying now

1102
00:42:36,070 --> 00:42:38,010
to get any lead from you.

1103
00:42:39,230 --> 00:42:40,490
They finally succeeded,

1104
00:42:40,510 --> 00:42:42,010
took down the criminal group,

1105
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:44,210
and rescued those girls,

1106
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,090
which also

1107
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,820
protected even more children.

1108
00:42:54,670 --> 00:42:56,050
So you're a hero?

1109
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,440
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

1110
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:44,960
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

1111
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:52,400
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

1112
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:56,320
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

1113
00:43:56,520 --> 00:44:00,200
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

1114
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:07,640
♪Where the days begin and end♪

1115
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:15,280
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

1116
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:22,640
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

1117
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:26,640
♪Through every passing season♪

1118
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:30,480
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

1119
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:34,560
♪Turn around and look♪

1120
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:38,560
♪That door's still open♪

1121
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:42,400
♪A light still burning♪

1122
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:46,200
♪Waiting there for you♪

1123
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,880
♪Turn around and look♪

1124
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:53,960
♪Someone's still waiting♪

1125
00:44:54,040 --> 00:44:57,760
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

1126
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,520
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

1127
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:06,960
♪It's always there♪
